     <body>
     <div type="to_the_reader">
   <pb facs="3"/>
   <head>To the Reader.</head>
   <lg n="1">
      <head>I.</head>
      <l>
         <hi>I</hi> Call'd the bushin'd Muse <hi>MELPOMENE,</hi>
      </l>
      <l>And told her what sad Storie I would write,</l>
      <l>Shee wept at hearing such a Tragedie:</l>
      <l>Though wont in mournefull Ditties to delight.</l>
      <l>If thou dislike these sorrowfull lines; Then know</l>
      <l>My Muse with teares not with Conceits did flow.</l>
   </lg>
   <lg n="2">
      <head>II.</head>
      <l>And as she my vnabler quill did guide,</l>
      <l>Her briny teares did on the paper fall,</l>
      <l>If then vnequall numbers be espied,</l>
      <l>Oh Reader! doe not that my error call,</l>
      <l>But thinke her teares defac't it, and blame then</l>
      <l>My Muses griefe, and not my missing Pen.</l>
   </lg>
   <closer>
      <signed>ABRA: COVVLEY.</signed>
   </closer>
</div>
